NDFSK statement on celebrations of Kim Jong Il's birthday 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, March 4 (KCNA) -- The central committee of the National Democratic Front of South Korea (NDFSK) on Friday issued a statement on the events held in celebration of leader Kim Jong Il's birthday, according to Seoul-based Radio Voice of National Salvation.
 According to the statement, the NDFSK central committee formed a "preparatory committee for celebrating the birthday of the great leader comrade Kim Jong Il" and held colorful functions in the period from Feb. 1 to 28. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A celebration meeting was held by the NDFSK central committee on Feb. 15. It was stressed there that the birth of  Kim Jong Il as the bright star of Mt. Paektu carrying forward the cause of the sun was the greatest fortune noteworthy in the 5,000-year history of the nation as well as a historic event which promised a rosy future of the country and the nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The meeting noted that Kim Jong Il was the first in human history to realize the cause of perpetuating the memory of President Kim Il Sung on the highest level. With the distinguished leadership ability and ever-victorious army-based policy, he safeguarded the peace of the Korean peninsula and security of the nation without the slightest wavering despite the imperialist allied forces' desperate moves to isolate and stifle the DPRK and opened up the road for turning the north into a powerful state and achieving a great national prosperity in the new century, it recalled. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Under his guidance, national reunification and the human cause of independence are sure to be realized and the new century will shine as a glorious Kim Jong Il century, it held. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Similar meetings were also held by provincial and city committees of the NDFSK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The meetings adopted congratulatory messages, letters and letters of pledge to Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 All the organizations under the NDFSK and patriotic movement organizations held colorful political and cultural events in conformity with their specific conditions. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The NDFSK mission in Pyongyang called a press conference in Pyongyang on Feb. 14. at the conference it introduced in detail the mind-set of South Korean people deeply revering and following Kim Jong Il as the sun of the 21st century and the lodestar of national reunification and clarified their firm will to bring earlier the dawn of national reunification.

KCNA on Bush's mud-slinging at DPRK's political system 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, March 4 (KCNA) -- U.S. President Bush malignantly slandered the dignified political system in the DPRK terming it a "closed system" in a "speech" made at the head office of the "Voice of America" in Washington on Feb. 25.
 His string of remarks against the DPRK's political system came in the wake of his malignant mud-slinging at the supreme headquarters of the DPRK and his call for a "change" in its system during his recent South Korea visit. This cannot but be interpreted as a very serious issue as it is not a mere provocation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He is foolish enough to seek to divorce the supreme headquarters from the people and infuse the U.S. view on value and the consciousness of "liberty" into its society while putting military pressure upon the DPRK in a bid to force it to "change" its system as what happened in those countries where capitalism revived. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. brought the weak political force Taliban to a collapse by hurling huge armed forces into the afghan war. It has become so arrogant as to officially declare as its state policy its projected foreign policy of aggression intended to put all the countries advocating independence under the U.S.-led neo-colonialist system. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Bush administration's bellicose plan to bring about a "change" in the DPRK's political system is to implement this policy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 By setting out such "policy" bush and u.s. foreign policy-makers only revealed that they are politically half witted. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK's political system is a man-centred system where the leader, the party and the masses form a harmonious whole. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 To try to force the DPRK to "change" it is just like sweeping the sea with a broom. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They should know this at least if they have a normal way of thinking and elementary reason. It is the Bush administration's tragedy that it is running amuck, not aware of who is its opponent. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The army and people of the DPRK regard it as their top priority to devotedly defend the supreme headquarters, their destiny and future, and will never pardon those who dare slander it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK army's strike is limitless and merciless and there is no place on this planet to escape it.

U.S. cock-and-bull stories rebuffed 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, March 4 (KCNA) -- Wolfowitz, U.S. deputy defense secretary, told nonsense that the DPRK is the "world's biggest exporter of ballistic missiles and their technology" and the director of the U.S. Central Intelligence Agency asserted that North Korea is a "major state that exports ballistic missile technology."
 Commenting on this, Rodong Sinmun today says: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is the height of sarcasm that the United States unreasonably pulls up the DPRK over its missile plan for self-defence despite the fact that the U.S. is the world's biggest producer and exporter of weapons and other military equipment. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The cock-and-bull stories about the DPRK floated by the U.S. ruling quarters are nothing but the last-ditch effort to get out of the present impasse. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They are now much upset after Bush's remarks about "the axis of evil" created furore throughout the world and touched off worldwide protest and condemnation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They are, therefore, playing a cheap trick to divert the international criticism directed to them to the DPRK at any cost. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Such sheer sophism and petty trick can never work on the world community today. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 No matter how loudly the bush ruling quarters may trumpet, no one will believe it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The people's army and people of Korea are becoming increasingly assertive that there can be no compromise with the U.S. and they should fight it out. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. is well advised to stop playing a cheap trick.

Yomju Youth Fish Farm 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, March 4 (KCNA) -- The Yomju Youth Fish Farm has been reconstructed on an expansion basis in Korea.
 The fish farm in Yomju county, North Phyongan Province in the northwestern part of the country, has a history of over 20 years. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It covers nearly one million m2. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 More than 80 fish ponds of different sizes have been built. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The fish farm has planned to catch fish from April. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is to breed such fresh water fish and seafish as carp, crucians and mullet as well as shellfish and shrimps. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is experienced in artificially incubating shrimps and mullet. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 And it is also expected to produce rare fishes including king crab, blue crab and globefish. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The fish farm has a duck farm with a capacity of hundreds of tons to provide fish meal.

Efficacious anti-cancer injection developed 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, March 4 (KCNA) -- A research group of the x-ray institute of the academy of medical science of the DPRK developed injection gallium microsphres (66ga), an efficacious medicine for the treatment of cancer.
 The injection was manufactured on the basis of strong effect of "-ray from 66ga killing cancer cells. This is injected into cancer region to treat the first and second stage mammary cancer and idiopathic liver cancer. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It can be used to cure brain cancer, etc. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Medicinal substance works within the radius of 4cm. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The injection has no sideeffect and no special substance for immunity revival is needed as the medicinal substance remains only in cancer region and has no immunity-resisting effect. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Unlike operation, the injection causes little pain and burden to the patients. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The results of the four-year-long treatment of over 50 patients suffering from first and second stage mammary cancer and idiopathic liver cancer, with affected region reaching up to 7cm, showed that all of them have been fully cured.
